FT  13 AUG 93 / Technology: Beet takes a beating - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An artificial sugar beet with built-in electronic sensors should give
farmers plenty to chew over this harvest.
Every year farmers are vexed by the amount of beet that gets damaged during
harvesting. As much as a third can be harmed by the harvesting machinery.
Help is at hand in the form of battery-powered sugar beet from Adas, the
agricultural development service. It is thrown in with the ordinary beet and
bumps through the harvester alongside it.
Electronic sensors, contained within a thin, carbon fibre shield and a
coating of rubber, reveal where most damage occurs during the process. Adas:
UK, 0525 860077.
