FT  13 AUG 93 / Technology: Notepad/notebook with the flip of a lid - Worth
Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A personal word processor with a traditional keyboard and a liquid crystal
screen which accepts hand-written script has been launched in Japan by
Sharp.
The WD-A770 has been designed with a 'swing-top' lid: when the keyboard is
used the machine sits open resembling a standard clam-shell notebook
machine; when the user wants to write on the notepad the screen is pulled
forward and laid on top of the keyboard, screen uppermost. Using a pen the
screen is used like a notepad, for creating illustrations or for editing, or
highlighting text.
Various thicknesses or modes of writing are built into the software. Sharp:
Japan, 06 625 3007.
