FT  13 AUG 93 / Recession curbs truck numbers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE number of trucks above 3.5 tonnes gross vehicle weight operating in the
UK fell by nearly 3.5 per cent last year to 415,000.
Truck sales have more than halved since the peak reached in 1989.
The total stock of trucks licensed in the UK is at its lowest level for 10
years, according to a report published yesterday by the Department of
Transport.
The decline was partly due to the recession but it also reflected the
continuing trend towards the use of heavier vehicles, according to the
report.
