FT  13 AUG 93 / DSS may face Pounds 67m bill over tax relief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Department of Social Services said yesterday it may have to pay up to
Pounds 67m in retroactive national insurance contribution rebates to
personal pension holders whose applications for tax relief went missing up
to four years ago, Norma Cohen writes.
The DSS said it had reached agreement with the Association of British
Insurers on some 32,000 personal pension plans for which original
applications for tax relief cannot be found.
Under terms of the agreement, ABI member companies could have to pay Pounds
6m to Pounds 7m to clients to bring investment returns into line with what
they would have been had the tax rebates been received on time.
