<TEXT>
The governent of Togo, a leading phosphates producer, has offered to buy
into a big fertilisers complex at Gela in Sicily, lying idle for the past
year, Haig Simonian reports from Milan.
The Gela complex includes ISAF, which produces sulphuric and phosphoric
