FT  12 AUG 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australian wool prices continued to slip this week, with the market
indicator declining slightly each selling day. Demand was insufficient to
lead to a good clearance at any of the sales and the overall proportion
passed in was nearly 15%. The Wool Corporation's market indicator at 434
cents a kg is now 10 cents below its closing level in June. After a hopeful
opening day the market is again illustrating the inadequacy of demand in
relation to supply. Recession is mentioned as a major cause and the absence
of the old Soviet Union is of even greater basic importance.
