FT  12 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Metal Bulletin advances 22%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Metal Bulletin, the international business publisher, raised pre-tax profits
by 22 per cent from Pounds 711,600 to Pounds 871,300 in the six months to
June 30 and, based on current activity levels, there was optimism that five
consecutive years of growth would be extended in 1993.
Mr Trevor Tarring, chairman, said the period had seen a continuation of the
growth pattern first experienced late in 1992 by the metals, futures and
options and managed funds divisions.
The minerals information side continued to be a solid contributor to
profits, while the textiles division - acquired at the end of 1992 - had
been successfully integrated and was exceeding its budget for turnover and
profit.
Group turnover expanded 19 per cent to Pounds 6.91m (Pounds 5.81m). Earnings
per 10p share rose from 5.1p to 6p and an increased interim dividend of 2.9p
(2.7p) is declared.
