<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 93 / Labour accuses the government of undermining local democracy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LABOUR yesterday accused the government of undermining local democracy by
expanding the powers and membership of quangos (quasi-autonomous
non-governmental organisations).
Mr Doug Henderson, shadow local government minister, said a Labour survey
suggested that quangos in some parts of Britain would soon have more members
than local authorities.
Quangos would be further boosted by more schools opting out of local
authority control, and more hospitals choosing to operate as self-governing
trusts.
The Audit Commission has announced a review of probity in local government,
to report in November.
