<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 93 / Audit Commission announces a review of probity in local
government
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Audit Commission has announced a review of probity in local government.
This arises from fears that its present method of measurement, which adds
all convictions for fraud of more than Pounds 500, might be underestimating
the scale of the problem.
The commission said fraud reported to it by auditors had increased each year
over the past three years, and a number of alleged corruption cases had been
passed to the police for investigation.
Publication of the review of fraud, which may include recommendations for
legislation, is expected in November.
