<TEXT>
ISRAEL'S Supreme Court put off a ruling yesterday on whether Mr John
Demjanjuk, acquitted of being Nazi killer 'Ivan the Terrible', should face
new war crime charges, as demanded by some death camp survivors, Reuter
reports from Jerusalem. Attorney General Yosef Harish told the court that
