<TEXT>
STATE floodplain managers have begun working with the White House to develop
new approaches to flood control, in the wake of the devastating Mississippi
floods, George Graham writes. Mr Larry Larson, head of the floodplain
management and dam safety programmes for Wisconsin and executive director of
the Association of State Floodplain Managers, said yesterday his
organisation had begun to work with Vice President Al Gore to find better
ways of keeping people out of harm's way. He warned that many earthwork
levees along the river were only designed to contain much lesser degrees of
flooding.
President Bill Clinton will sign a Dollars 6.3bn flood relief bill today in
St Louis, Reuter reports. The government slashed projections for corn and
soybean harvests and said crop losses are expected to total Dollars 2.5bn.
